---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<style>
  .fd-cards-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: row;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding: 0 5rem;
  }

  .fd-card {
    flex: 1;
    flex-basis: 30%;
    background: rgba(26, 42, 69, 0.6);
    border: 1px solid rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.2);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .fd-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.4);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.1);
    transform: translateY(-4px);
  }

  .fd-card-header {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.15);
    background: rgba(10, 22, 40, 0.4);
  }

  .fd-card-header :global(.fd-section-heading) {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #3ee8b5;
  }

  .fd-card-body {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    flex-grow: 1;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .fd-card-body :global(.fd-paragraph) {
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #e8e4df;
  }

  .fd-card-body :global(.fd-list) {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .fd-card-body :global(.fd-list-item) {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: #e8e4df;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
</style>
<p class="fd-paragraph">
  Healthcare coordination is complex — a single patient may need benefits support, engagement outreach, medical records retrieval, and ongoing health monitoring simultaneously, each involving different staff and requiring full auditability for compliance. Machina's workflow engine is purpose-built to orchestrate this reality at scale.
</p>

<h2 class="fd-section-heading">Process</h2>

<p class="fd-paragraph">
  A workflow progresses through defined phases, automatically generating the right tasks for the right people at the right time — while recording every transition for operational analysis and regulatory compliance.
</p>

<figure class="fd-inline-figure">
  <img
    src={`${base}/visualizations/parent-child-workflow.png`}
    alt="Three-phase workflow lifecycle: Workflow Creation, Task Creation, and Ten-Step Task Completion Pipeline"
    class="fd-inline-img"
    style="max-width: 90%;"
    loading="lazy"
  />
</figure>

<h2 class="fd-section-heading">Benefits</h2>

<p class="fd-paragraph">
  Machina's workflow engine doesn't just track status — it actively coordinates care across every role, every process, and every compliance requirement. Organizations gain the flexibility to model their exact care processes, and have the visibility needed to keep costs down and patients engaged.
</p>

<p class="fd-paragraph">
  Because every status transition, task assignment, and queue interaction is stored as a temporal record, the system is a rich source of operational intelligence — time-in-status analysis, bottleneck detection, workload distribution, SLA compliance rates, and workflow outcome analysis are all queryable without additional instrumentation.
</p>

<figure class="fd-inline-figure">
  <img
    src={`${base}/visualizations/workflow-benefits.png`}
    alt="Three-phase workflow lifecycle: Workflow Creation, Task Creation, and Ten-Step Task Completion Pipeline"
    class="fd-inline-img"
    loading="lazy"
  />
</figure>

<div class="fd-cards-container">

  <div class="fd-card">
    <div class="fd-card-header">
      <h2 class="fd-section-heading">Configurable</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="fd-card-body">
      <p class="fd-paragraph">
        Every healthcare organization runs slightly different care processes — one company's benefits support workflow may have 13 statuses with conditional branching, another may have 5.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="fd-card">
    <div class="fd-card-header">
      <h2 class="fd-section-heading">Child Workflows</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="fd-card-body">
      <p class="fd-paragraph">
        A single workflow can spawn child workflows. For example, the comprehensive patient journey would contain both an engagement process and a benefits support process.
      </p>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>


  <div class="fd-card">
    <div class="fd-card-header">
      <h2 class="fd-section-heading">Multi-role work</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="fd-card-body">
      <p class="fd-paragraph">
        Field personnel, nurse practitioners, SOAR specialists, and medical records teams each see only their assigned work
      </p>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="fd-card">
    <div class="fd-card-header">
      <h2 class="fd-section-heading">Auditing &amp; Compliance</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="fd-card-body">
      <p class="fd-paragraph">
        Every status transition is recorded with precise start and end timestamps to create an unbroken audit trail: 
        <li class="fd-list-item">What happened</li>
        <li class="fd-list-item">When it happened</li>
        <li class="fd-list-item">How long each phase lasted</li>
        <li class="fd-list-item">Who was responsible</li>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>
